{"user_message": {"title": "Architecture Review — ai-bookkeeper (week of 2026-05-28): ADR 0005, Money-Formatting Consolidation", "content": "## ADR 0005 — Consolidate money formatting onto one shared kernel; adopt `formatMoney` app-wide\n**Status: Proposed** · extends ADR 0004/0003/0002/0001 · written to `docs/adr/0005-money-formatting-consolidation.md`\n\n### Context (what the codebase actually shows)\nThe weekly trace looked beyond the ledger feature at how *every* feature renders money. The headline finding: **ADR 0004's `formatMoney` is orphaned — zero consumers.** There are three parallel money paths:\n\n| Path | Currency-aware? | `roundMoney`-normalized (drift-free)? | Fail-loud? | Consumers |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `features/ledger/lib/format.ts` → `formatMoney` (ADR 0004) | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | **0** |\n| `src/lib/format.ts` → `formatCurrency`/`formatSignedCurrency` | ❌ USD-only | ❌ | ❌ | **9** |\n| `WealthScoreCard.tsx:195` inline `` `$${(v/1e6).toFixed(1)}M` `` | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | 1 |\n\nSo ADR 0004's core promise — *what the user sees is provably what the ledger stored* — is **unrealized in the product**. Every visible balance flows through the un-normalized, USD-hard-coded path (9 sites: benchmarks ×2, customers ×2, tax-credits ×2, wealth-score, ledger TransactionsCard).\n\n**Layering smell (evidence):** `@/features/ledger` is already a de-facto shared kernel — 5 feature modules import `type Transaction` from it. But the money *primitives* (round/arithmetic/format) live inside `features/ledger/lib`, so any feature wanting drift-free money must take a **feature→feature** dependency on `ledger`. The correct home for cross-cutting domain primitives is a shared kernel.\n\n### Decision\nConverge on **one** money authority. **No new primitive is needed** — this is adoption + consolidation of what ADR 0002–0004 already built:\n1. Promote `round/arithmetic/format` to a shared `src/lib/money/` kernel (removes feature→feature coupling).\n2. Reimplement `src/lib/format.ts` `formatCurrency`/`formatSignedCurrency` as thin wrappers over `formatMoney(_, \"USD\")` — drift-free + fail-loud everywhere with zero call-site churn day one.\n3. Re-point the 9 consumers; retire the un-normalized path; replace WealthScore's inline abbreviator with a kernel `formatMoneyCompact`.\n4. Lint guardrail forbidding raw `` `$${…}` ``/`toFixed` on money outside `src/lib/money`.\n\n*Alternative considered* — anoint `@/features/ledger` as the official kernel — **rejected**: cements a feature as everyone's dependency. The shared-kernel move costs one extra step while only 5 imports exist.\n\n### Task breakdown (12 pts total)\n1. Create `src/lib/money/` kernel; move round+arithmetic+format+tests; barrel; keep ledger re-export 1 release — **3 pts**\n2. `formatCurrency`/`formatSignedCurrency` → wrappers over `formatMoney` (preserve `+`/`−`; golden-string tests) — **2 pts**\n3. Re-point 9 components; delete dead paths — **2 pts**\n4. Replace WealthScore inline `$…M/$…K` with kernel `formatMoneyCompact` + tests — **2 pts**\n5. ESLint guardrail on raw money templates — **2 pts**\n6. **(Recurring)** Fix release-gate blocker `src/app/page.tsx:9` `` → `next/link` `` — **1 pt**\n\n```chart\nKernel move (T1): 3\nWrappers (T2): 2\nRe-point 9 sites (T3): 2\nCompact helper (T4): 2\nLint guardrail (T5): 2\nLint blocker (T6): 1\n```\n\n### Notes\n- **Verdict:** No new money code; the gap is adoption + structural consolidation.\n- **Recurring blocker:** `page.tsx:9` lint error (flagged in ADR 0004 Task 6) is **still open** — `eslint .` is still red, so the release gate stays blocked regardless of feature quality.\n- **UNVERIFIED:** `formatSignedCurrency` uses U+2212 `−`; the wrapper must preserve it (golden-string test) to avoid a silent shift to ASCII `-`.\n- **Tooling note:** Obsidian shared-vault MCP tools were not available in this run; prior-decision continuity was taken from the repo ADR log (0001–0004) + persona memory instead.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

